body:
Great, thanks @jorgelbg. Am +1 to commit this.

@chrismattmann what about taking small incremental steps and commit NUTCH-2102 first then modify it so that it can handle the formats done by the CCDD?

In practice the CCDD is of little use even on medium sized crawls as it does not do HDFS and mapreduce unlike NUTCH-2102. If you think about CommonCrawl who would be the main users of the WARC exporter and given the volume of data they deal with, NUTCH-2102 is probably the option they'll go for. They already have some code for it, sure, but I'd rather they used and contributed to stuff which is in our codebase

@jorgelbg what about 
`git diff --no-prefix trunk..warc > NUTCH-2095.patch`
attach it to the JIRA, patch then commit on SVN? This way the JIRA issue will have the patch and you'll be able to modify the CHANGES.txt as well

Implemented in [23c7761aff83]

@chrismattmann I don't expect that this would change anything to the existing functionalities of CCDD. @jorgelbg can you confirm?

Can we close this PR?

@sebastian-nagel Thanks for the suggestions. Please have a look at the updated code.

p.s. 
   I admit I am new  to `ant` so I request your special attention to changes in the build files
